title: Google Cloud Platform: A Tour into recent features and What to expect from Google Cloud Next
description: Google Cloud Platform has seen significant momentum in the last year with key platform differentiators and a growing customer base. This talk takes you through a whirlwind tour of key GCP differentiators and some key features that have been released over the last several months.

title: Only with Apps Script
description: With most businesses adapting G Suite to collaborate and optimize their workflows, there's an opportunity for makers to use it's low-code developer platform and leverage its capabilities to build things that can only be done using the Apps Script ecosystem viz. Add-ons & Data Studio Community Connectors.

title: Reimagine Work with AI/ ML, Chatbots, & Connected Systems over G Suite
description: This talk will enable businessmen to do "EVERYTHING" on G Suite, Google's Productivity, and Collaboration Suite. A complete Google Solution can lead to up to 2/3rd savings on Technology and up to 10X increase in productivity for organizations. In this talk, we shall focus on AI/ML facilities in G Suite, Chat Rooms, and Chatbots on Google Chat and how you can truly transform work by connecting your ERP/ CRM with G Suite and live and breath completely on Cloud.

title: What's new in Google Compute Engine
description: Google Compute Engine is an infrastructure service provided as part of the Google Cloud Platform. It is available at several Google data centers worldwide and is provided exclusively on an on-demand basis.

title: Demistifying Containers
description: Containers are quickly becoming an industry standard for the deployment of software applications. The business and technological advantages of containerizing workloads are driving many teams towards moving their applications to containers. Docker plays a vital role in putting up pieces together to easily running containers anywhere. Containerized applications have changed the game and are here to stay and have already become a de-facto standard for application delivery. With Kubernetes, you can orchestrate containers with ease, and integration with the Google Cloud Platform is seamless. It demonstrates the lifecycle of an application transitioning from a traditional VM/OS-based deployment to a specialized os for containers to a platform for containers better known as GKE.

title: Using Skaffold for building and deploying applications to GKE
description: Skaffold handles the workflow for building, pushing, and deploying your application, allowing you to focus on what matters most. Want to know the logic behind this magic? Great! Vishal Biyani from InfraCloud Technologies is here who possess vast experience in this field.

title: CDN Delivery on the go
description: As the name implies, a Content Delivery Network is primarily responsible for delivering content such as web pages, images, videos, and data to users globally, by using a network of servers distributed throughout a number of different geographic locations. Sounds Great No? To know more about this under the hood technology, we have Praveen Thirumurugan from Caterpillar Inc. who sharing his insightful words.
